## Special Cases

### Metadata XML schema reference

Before generating any metadata XML file (CustomObject, Flow, ApexClass, Platform Event, etc.), use `Salesforce DX` code-analysis tools or `WebFetch` from the [Metadata API Developer Guide](https://developer.salesforce.com/docs/atlas.en-us.api_meta.meta/api_meta/meta_intro.htm) to confirm schema shape and valid field values.

### When DX requires context not yet available

`user-Salesforce DX` tools require `usernameOrAlias` and `directory` parameters. If the session has not yet resolved the org alias:
1. Call `user-Salesforce DX` → `get_username` first to resolve the alias.
2. If `get_username` fails, fall back to SF CLI: `sf org display`.
3. Once the alias is known, proceed with the intended DX tool.

### Read-only vs write classification

| Category | Tools | Confirmation required |
|---|---|---|
| **Read-only** | `run_soql_query`, `retrieve_metadata` (dry-run), `get_username`, `list_all_orgs`, `scan_apex_class_for_antipatterns`, `run_code_analyzer`, all `guide_*`, all `explore_*`, all `fetch_*`, all `create_*` (metadata file generation — local only) | No |
| **Write (org-changing)** | `deploy_metadata`, `run_apex_test` (when deploying), `assign_permission_set`, SF CLI data mutation commands (`sf data create record`, `sf data update record`) | Yes — follow the agent's two-gate protocol |
